Lab Demo Steps:
1. Create a new project in Pycharm
2. Set interpreter
3. Add Pyspark dependency
4. Execute the project


1. Create a new project in Pycharm
Download Python and PyCharm and them click new project
2. Set interpreter
File> Settings> Project name> Python interpreter(make sure interpreter is the same as the python version you have 
3. Add Pyspark dependency
Open terminal> type pip install pypandoc> enter
To Install pyspark> Type pip --no-cache-dir install pyspark > Enter
verify by going back to settings>project name> interpreter> should be listed in packages under interpreter
4. Execute the project
